    <h1 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">WAPDA Online Bill Check — All DISCOs 2026 Guide</h1>

    <p class="text-neutral-600 text-lg mb-4">"WAPDA bill" is the colloquial term most Pakistanis still use for their monthly electricity bill — even though WAPDA (Water and Power Development Authority) was split into separate power-generation and distribution companies in the late 1990s. Today, electricity distribution is handled by <strong>11 separate Distribution Companies (DISCOs)</strong>, each serving a specific region of Pakistan. To check your "WAPDA bill" online, you first need to know which DISCO serves your area — then visit the right bill checker and enter your 14-digit reference number. This guide covers all 11 DISCOs, helps you identify yours, and walks you through the online bill-check process step by step.</p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-l-4 border-primary-600 p-4 rounded-lg mb-8">
      <p class="font-semibold text-primary-800">Quick Summary: Find your DISCO below → visit its bill checker on pakistanbill.online → enter your 14-digit reference number (top-right of any previous bill, labeled "Ref. No.") → click "Check Bill" → download PDF if needed. Free, instant, no login.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">All 11 WAPDA DISCOs — Find Yours</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Each DISCO serves a specific geographic area. Find your city in the table below to identify your DISCO:</p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg">
        <thead class="bg-neutral-100">
          <tr>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">DISCO</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Major Cities / Areas</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Coverage Province</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Checker</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-neutral-200">
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">LESCO</td><td class="p-3">Lahore, Kasur, Okara, Sheikhupura</td><td class="p-3">Punjab (central)</td><td class="p-3"><a href="/lesco-bill/" class="text-primary-600">/lesco-bill/</a></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">IESCO</td><td class="p-3">Islamabad, Rawalpindi, Jhelum, Attock</td><td class="p-3">ICT + North Punjab</td><td class="p-3"><a href="/iesco-bill/" class="text-primary-600">/iesco-bill/</a></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">FESCO</td><td class="p-3">Faisalabad, Jhang, Sargodha, Toba Tek Singh</td><td class="p-3">Punjab (central)</td><td class="p-3"><a href="/fesco-bill/" class="text-primary-600">/fesco-bill/</a></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">GEPCO</td><td class="p-3">Gujranwala, Gujrat, Sialkot, Mandi Bahauddin</td><td class="p-3">Punjab (north)</td><td class="p-3"><a href="/gepco-bill/" class="text-primary-600">/gepco-bill/</a></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">MEPCO</td><td class="p-3">Multan, Bahawalpur, Dera Ghazi Khan, Sahiwal</td><td class="p-3">Punjab (south)</td><td class="p-3"><a href="/mepco-bill/" class="text-primary-600">/mepco-bill/</a></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">PESCO</td><td class="p-3">Peshawar, Mardan, Abbottabad, Charsadda</td><td class="p-3">KP (settled districts)</td><td class="p-3"><a href="/pesco-bill/" class="text-primary-600">/pesco-bill/</a></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">TESCO</td><td class="p-3">Bajaur, Kurram, Waziristan, Khyber, Mohmand, Orakzai</td><td class="p-3">KP (tribal/merged districts)</td><td class="p-3"><a href="/tesco-bill/" class="text-primary-600">/tesco-bill/</a></td></tr>
