    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">If you're not sure which DISCO serves your city, check any previous bill — the DISCO name is printed at the top of the bill (e.g., "LESCO Electricity Bill" or "IESCO Electricity Bill").</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Step-by-Step: How to Check Your WAPDA Bill Online</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">The process is identical for all 11 DISCOs:</p>
    <ol class="space-y-3 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-decimal list-inside">
      <li><strong>Identify your DISCO</strong> using the table above or by checking any previous bill.</li>
      <li><strong>Find your 14-digit reference number</strong> on any previous bill. It's printed in bold on the <strong>top-right section</strong>, labeled "Ref. No." or "Reference No.", directly above the barcode. It contains only digits — no letters or dashes.</li>
      <li><strong>Open your DISCO's bill checker</strong> on pakistanbill.online (URLs in the table above).</li>
      <li><strong>Enter the 14-digit reference number.</strong> Type carefully, count the digits, and double-check for missing leading zeros.</li>
      <li><strong>Click "Check Bill".</strong> Your current month's bill loads in 2–5 seconds.</li>
      <li><strong>Review the bill details</strong>: consumer name, address, billing month, units consumed, total amount, due date.</li>
      <li><strong>Download PDF</strong> if you want a duplicate copy. The PDF is identical to the printed bill and is accepted at all payment channels.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What Information Shows on a WAPDA Bill?</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">All DISCO bills follow the same WAPDA-derived format. Key fields you'll see:</p>
    <div class="bg-neutral-900 text-green-400 font-mono rounded-xl p-5 mb-6 text-sm overflow-x-auto">
      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-xs mb-2">// WAPDA Bill — Top Right Section</p>
      <p>┌─────────────────────────────────┐</p>
      <p>│  [DISCO NAME] Electricity Bill     │</p>
      <p>│  Consumer: [Your Name]            │</p>
      <p>│  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │</p>
      <p class="text-yellow-300">│  │ <strong>Ref. No: 01234567890123</strong>  │   │ ← 14-digit</p>
      <p>│  │ Customer ID: 1234567890  │   │</p>
      <p>│  │ Reading Date: 12-June-26 │   │</p>
      <p>│  │ Units Consumed: 320 kWh  │   │</p>
      <p>│  │ Current Bill: Rs. 12,450 │   │</p>
      <p>│  │ FPA: Rs. 980             │   │</p>
      <p>│  │ Total Payable: Rs. 13,430│   │</p>
      <p>│  │ Due Date: 28-June-2026   │   │</p>
      <p>│  └──────────────────────────┘   │</p>
      <p>│  [████████ BARCODE ████████]    │</p>
      <p>└─────────────────────────────────┘</p>
    </div>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">Watch out for these common bill line items:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Current Bill:</strong> Base charge for units consumed this month, plus fixed charges</li>
      <li><strong>FPA (Fuel Price Adjustment):</strong> Government-passed-through charge based on international fuel prices. Varies monthly.</li>
      <li><strong>QTR (Quarterly Tariff Adjustment):</strong> NEPRA-approved adjustment every 3 months</li>
      <li><strong>FC Surcharge:</strong> Debt servicing surcharge for power-sector loans (Rs. 0.43/kWh)</li>
      <li><strong>Electricity Duty:</strong> Provincial tax (1–1.5% of current bill)</li>
      <li><strong>TV Fee:</strong> Rs. 35/month PTV fee (mandatory for all connections)</li>
      <li><strong>Bank Charges:</strong> Rs. 15/month bank processing fee</li>
      <li><strong>Arrears:</strong> Unpaid amount from previous months (if any)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Tips to Avoid Bill Issues</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-3 text-neutral-600 mb-6 list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Save your reference number</strong> in your phone's notes — saves time every month.</li>
      <li><strong>Check your bill online 5–7 days before due date</strong> — printed bills sometimes arrive after due date.</li>
      <li><strong>Compare units consumed</strong> with your meter reading. If bill shows 350 kWh but your meter shows 280 kWh, request a correction at your DISCO office.</li>
      <li><strong>Stay under 200 units per month</strong> to qualify for NEPRA's Protected Consumer subsidy (about 30–40% discount per unit).</li>
      <li><strong>Pay before the 25th</strong> of each month — banks and shops have long queues near due dates.</li>
      <li><strong>Keep payment receipts for 3 months</strong> in case of dispute.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-10">
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">How to check WAPDA bill online?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Identify your DISCO (LESCO for Lahore, IESCO for Islamabad, etc.) and visit pakistanbill.online → select your DISCO → enter your 14-digit reference number. Your WAPDA electricity bill loads instantly — free, no login.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">What is the WAPDA reference number?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">The WAPDA reference number is a 14-digit number printed on the top-right of your electricity bill, labeled 'Ref. No.', directly above the barcode. It contains only digits, no letters. It stays the same every month.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Which DISCO covers my city?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Lahore=LESCO, Islamabad/Rawalpindi=IESCO, Faisalabad=FESCO, Gujranwala=GEPCO, Multan=MEPCO, Peshawar=PESCO, Hyderabad=HESCO, Sukkur=SEPCO, Quetta=QESCO, Tribal KP=TESCO, Karachi=K-Electric, Azad Kashmir=AJK WAPDA.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Can I download WAPDA bill PDF?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Yes. After checking your bill online, click 'Download PDF' to save a duplicate copy. The PDF is identical to the printed bill and is accepted at all banks, JazzCash, EasyPaisa, and 1Bill retailers for payment.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Is WAPDA bill check free?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">Yes. Checking your WAPDA bill online at pakistanbill.online is completely free. There are no fees, no subscriptions, and no login required. We only ask for your 14-digit reference number — no CNIC or personal information needed.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">What is FPA on my WAPDA bill?</summary><div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">FPA stands for Fuel Price Adjustment. It's a government-passed-through charge based on international fuel prices. It varies monthly — can be Rs. 1–8 per kWh. FPA is the same across all DISCOs nationwide.</div></details>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-2xl p-6 mb-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="font-bold text-xl text-primary-900 mb-2">Check Your WAPDA Bill Now</h2>
      <p class="text-primary-700 mb-4 text-sm">Select your DISCO to get started.</p>
